James de Villiers, News 24 (NSRI website) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; Paddlers on Sunday discovered the body of a man in a life jacket in Zeekoevlei near Grassy Park on Sunday, the National Sea Rescue Institute (NSRI) confirmed.&nbsp; The paddlers&nbsp;spotted the body floating in a life-jacket near to a capsized boat while they were on an early morning paddle, NSRI station commander Vaughn Seconds said in a statement.&nbsp; By the time an NSRI team arrived at the scene, the paddlers had&nbsp;already brought the body to the shore.&nbsp; The NSRI couldn't immediately provide the man's age. Circumstances surrounding the incident are still unknown and police are investigating.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.